==English==
===Etymology===
Prefix [[hetero-]] + [[gene]] + [[-ous]].

===Adjective===
'''heterogeneous'''

# [[diverse|Diverse]] in [[kind]] or [[nature]]; [[composed]] of diverse [[part]]s.
# (''mathematics''): [[Incommensurable]] because of different kinds.
# {{physics}}: Having more than one [[phase]] ([[solid]], [[liquid]], [[gas]]) present in a [[system]] or [[process]].
# {{chemistry}}: Visibly consisting of different components.
# (''information technology''): A network comprising different types of computers, eventually with vastly differing memory sizes, processing power and even basic underlying architecture.

===Antonyms===
*[[homogeneous]]

